ides a theological interpretation of the events in the Book of Judith and puts forward the statement that God crushes wars. In the intertextual biblical dialogue, the Book of Judith is read as a plea for resistance to a violent regime, not with warlike means but through the strategic deployment of female beauty.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aTheology and Religious StudiesxOld Testament and Ancient Near EastxApocrypha and PseudepigraphaxApocrypha and Pseudepigrapha, others. 0aTheology and Religious StudiesxOld Testament and Ancient Near EastxIsrael and the Ancient Near EastxAncient Near East. 4aFeministische Theologie. 4aIntertextualität. 4aJudith (Buch). 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311017926240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089998640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110899986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110899986/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014